//www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>15</mn><mo>=C3=B7</mo><=
mn>5</mn><mo>=3D</mo><mn>3</mn><mtext>&nbsp;grams</mtext></mrow><annotation=
 encoding=3D"application/x-tex">15 \div 5 =3D 3 \text{ grams}</annotation><=
/semantics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><s=
pan class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut"></span><span class=3D"mord">15</sp=
an><span class=3D"mspace"></span><span class=3D"mbin">=C3=B7</span><span cl=
ass=3D"mspace"></span></span><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut"></s=
pan><span class=3D"mord">5</span><span class=3D"mspace"></span><span class=
=3D"mrel">=3D</span><span class=3D"mspace"></span></span><span class=3D"bas=
e"><span class=3D"strut"></span><span class=3D"mord">3</span><span class=3D=
"mord text"><span class=3D"mord">&nbsp;grams</span></span></span></span></s=
pan></span></p>
<h2 style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong>Why is Gram to Carat Conversion Imp=
ortant?</strong></h2>
<ol style=3D"text-align: left;">
<li>
<strong>For Jewelers &amp; Designers</strong> =E2=80=93 Jewelers need to en=
sure the correct gemstone weight for custom jewelry pieces.</li>
